# Software Engineer's Guide to AI Agents

## Overview
This book serves as a comprehensive guide for software engineers looking to understand and implement AI agents. 

## Contents

### Foundational Principles
- Large Language Models (LLMs)
- Core concepts: tokens, parameters, and Transformer architecture
- Function calling and tool integration

### AI Agents
- Autonomous planning and execution
- Tool utilization for complex goals
- Agent architectures and implementations

### Open Standards
- Model Context Protocol (MCP) for agent-tool interaction
- Agent-to-Agent (A2A) protocol for inter-agent communication
- Integration patterns for agentic systems

### Practical Implementation
- FastAPI integration
- Business service integration
- Human-in-the-Loop (HITL) considerations
- Real-world deployment strategies

